metadata.name: Until biodiversity rains #93
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork. 

In the interpretation of biological organisms, which break paradigms by doing something different, to adapt to changes and be able to survive, paths emerge to be imitated by so many, and make life flow. The development of the work is a metaphor for those paths full of ingenuity and risk, where colorful organisms in rows open trails, sliding like subtle drops, with sophisticated turns and elastic jumps.

Some alternative paths usually hide a message along the way. Literally, one could find and read phrases in relation to biodiversity and its importance. Although it is more common to ignore them, sometimes not respect them, or what is worse, forget them. Even so, in an exacerbated insistence, here, audiovisual organizations seem to be repeating themselves, “until biodiversity rains”, and variety exploits so that ecosystems finally go it alone.


Relationship between visuals and sounds:
Biological organisms of different colors follow a path. They move forward, change shape, stop, turn. Always one after the other. At certain moments, they stretch and jump and sounds emerge.

Towards the edges of the canvas, the jumps are translated into cello sounds, mainly pizzicatos. Towards the center, the piano. From the main jumps emerges a kind of melody played by a pseudo-theremin-synth, characterized by flyaway melodies with glissant.


This artwork is 100% code, made in p5.js + tone.js.

[ Click ]  -> sound ON / OFF
[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen
[ p ] -> pause / play 

Note: This artwork is an animated piece, and requires a powerful GPU for optimal real-time playback. It is important to note that it may not run properly on mobile devices, especially not high-end ones.
It is recommended to run the piece in a new window from the “open” button.

metadata.name: Dump of Links. Part II #87
metadata.description:
Audiovisual generative artwork. It continues with the proposal of the first part, revealing remote points of hills full of abandoned URLs, with a contemplative approach.

A ‘404 button’ shines from above, in the distance, as if it were a star that -possibly- watches over. And below, in a metaphor for pollution, rise islands of floating garbage. As if it were a calm, lonely, suffocating breath, and even sometimes dangerously attractive.

Original sound of voice, piano & synths.

[ s ] -> save 2160x2160px (in live view)
[ f ] -> fullscreen
[ q ] -> stop

Note: This artwork is an animated piece, and requires a powerful GPU for optimal real-time playback. It is important to note that it may not run properly on mobile devices, especially not high-end ones.

metadata.name: Radiant #222
metadata.description:
We were all born with a jewel in our heart – golden, shining.  Maybe you call it love, or the divine, or beauty.  The trials of life can cover up that jewel, and make it hard to see the beauty within.  We think we’re not worthy, not lovable.  But that’s a lie.  The jewel is always there.  You just need to clean off the gunk.  We are all made of love and supernovas.  You always were, and always will be - radiant.

Radiant was created generatively in p5.js.  Seven possible radial designs overlap on two canvases. On the top canvas, circles or arcs are erased to reveal the canvas below. There are four ways the background gets created, mostly using Perlin noise to pick colors from the palette. There are 34 hand-crafted palettes of 7 colors each. 

Original pixel density 1 with grain added automatically.
After pressing “open”:
2 – 5 to increase pixel density.  
g to add grain.  Adding grain takes a while at pixel density 5.
s to save a png.
Screen resize renders at pixel density 1.

I love sharing what I’ve learned about gen art and inspiring others on my YouTube channel, Steve’s Makerspace. Follow me there and on Twitter @stevemakerspace and Mastodon @stevesmakerspace.

metadata.name: Proto alphabet #104
metadata.description:
For more than 4000 years, before Lineal A in Crete, proto alphabets were created. They freed man from the chains of evolution and gave a way to record the rhythm of the passage of time.

As recursion generates a grammar, recursion generates the strokes that shape the following proto alphabets, which attempt to record the passage of time.

Time is the substance I am made of. Time is a river which sweeps me along, but I am the river; it is a tiger which destroys me, but I am the tiger; it is a fire which consumes me, but I am the fire. - Jorge Luis Borges


Desde hace más de 4000 años, antes Lineal A en Creta, proto alfabetos fueron creados. Liberaron al hombre de las cadenas de la evolución y dieron una forma para registrar el ritmo del paso del tiempo.

Como la recursividad genera una gramática, la recursividad genera los trazos que dan forma a los siguientes proto alfabetos, los cuales intentan registrar el paso del tiempo.

El tiempo es la sustancia de que estoy hecho. El tiempo es un río que me arrebata, pero yo soy el río; es un tigre que me destroza, pero yo soy el tigre; es un fuego que me consume, pero yo soy el fuego. - Jorge Luis Borges


Controls (in live view):
- Press s to get a PNG file
- Press S to get a SVG file

Artwork by x0y0z0 @x0y0z0tn (2023)

metadata.name: Bricks & Books #36
metadata.description:
Civil engineering and reading, two passions, two disciplines, numbers and letters. Construction and literature, two vocations so different and yet with such close souls.
They are both represented here by Bricks and Books paying a symbolic tribute to construction and literature in one collection.
The challenge was keeping them together in the same piece of code to be able to maintain the strength of the message and the aesthetic of the creation.

metadata.name: On the Grid #26
metadata.description:
On the Grid is a generative art project resulting in a unique 16/9 format world map.

This project is inspired by a 114cm x 76cm Lego world map that I created in real life. The coordinates of the continents are transpositions from this first project.

It is made using SVG and Vanilla JS with no libraries.

I hope you enjoy discovering On the Grid and minting your own unique world map.

Thanks for collecting!

metadata.name: Modulacions (audio) #66
metadata.description:
Modulacions (Modulations): modulation with an oscillator (carrier) with an LFO (modulator). 

-The LFO is controlled by  some of fxhash characters

-Some parameters are randomly assigned to each of the possible characters of the fxhash string (0,1,2....X,Y,Z): carrier frequency, maximum and minimum frequencies of the modulator, waveforms, views etc.

-A number of fxhash characters are selected (8,16,24,32, 40 or 48), and in order they are played and displayed using the assigned values.

-Each character is encoded in binary-> the LFO frequency is controlled: 1->maximum frequency, 0->minimum frequency.

Features:
·dark: black (true) or white (false).
·carrier_wave: wave shape of carrier oscillator (sine, square, triangle or sawtooth)
·modulator_mult: value of LFO multiplier.
·modulator_sum: value added to LFO amplitude.
·num_fxhash_chars: number of fxhash characters used (8,16,24,32, 40 or 48)
·bits_display: bits string visualization (3 types)
·carrier_freq_range: frequency range of carrier (low, mid or high).
·frames_per_bit: duration of each bit in frames.(15,20,25 or 30)

-NOTE: Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated.

-p5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: Modulacions 2: 'Memory' (audio) #30
metadata.description:
"Modulacions 2: Memory" ies the second piece of the series 'Modulations'. Shorter (at most 12 characters of the Fxhash string) but with memory that is displayed on the screen.

Modulacions (Modulations): modulation with an oscillator (carrier) with an LFO (modulator).

-The LFO is controlled by some of fxhash characters

-Some parameters are randomly assigned to each of the possible characters of the fxhash string (0,1,2....X,Y,Z): carrier frequency, maximum and minimum frequencies of the modulator, waveforms, views etc.

-A number of fxhash characters are selected (4,6,8 or 12), and in order they are played and displayed using the assigned values.

-Each character is encoded in binary-> the LFO frequency is controlled: 1->maximum frequency, 0->minimum frequency.

Features:
·dark: black (true) or white (false).
·carrier_wave: wave shape of carrier oscillator (sine, square, triangle or sawtooth)
·modulator_mult: value of LFO multiplier.
·modulator_sum: value added to LFO amplitude.
·num_fxhash_chars: number of fxhash characters used (4, 6 , 8 or 12)
·carrier_freq_range: frequency range of carrier (low, mid or high).
·frames_per_bit: duration of each bit in frames.(10, 15 or 20)
·one_visual: same visual for all chars (true) or nor (false).

Press 's' to save canvas as png.

-NOTES:
·Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated.
·Preview is randomly generated, the final result can be very different.

-p5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: System β #230
metadata.description:
α -> β is about "Increases in magnitude and decreases in computation". And still related the fleeting time in the generating process.

My role in this work is more of a discoverer than a creator. 

Try to reveal the possibilities of time perception in the generative art through negotiating with incomprehensible mathematical equations.

What I want to explore through this work is that behind the generated results, the dynamic process of generations are equally diverse and unpredictable.

When we watch the generating process displayed on the computer, changing instantly, moving, multiplying, disappearing, and we hesitate, wonder, pause, await, as if many possibilities of time perception have emerged in the fragmented moments.

_
press [1] -> β 
press [2] -> β⁰　 
press [3] -> β¹
-
Press [s] in live view to save as PNG.
Press [d] in live view to save as hi-res PNG.
-
If you need your collection in SVG format, feel free to DM me.
